{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7523b83f-3bfd-42ee-8f6a-95372795a214","content":"The directory only contains `.template.config/template.json` — no actual template content or packaging files. Here's my assessment:\n\n**✅ Present & correct:**\n- `identity`, `name`, `shortName`, `author` — all required fields\n- `classifications` and `tags` — good for discoverability\n- `sourceName` — enables name substitution\n- `symbols` with a `Framework` choice parameter\n\n**⚠️ Issues to fix before publishing:**\n\n1. **No `$schema`** — Add `\"$schema\": \"http://json.schemastore.org/template\"` for validation/editor support.\n2. **No `groupIdentity`** — Strongly recommended for NuGet (e.g., `\"groupIdentity\": \"MyCompany.WebApi\"`). Enables template grouping and updates.\n3. **Framework symbol has no `replaces`** — The `Framework` parameter won't substitute into project files unless you add `\"replaces\": \"net9.0\"` (or wire it via a generated symbol).\n4. **No template content** — There are no `.cs`, `.csproj`, or other source files for the template to scaffold.\n5. **No packaging project** — You need a `.csproj` (with `<PackageType>Template</PackageType>`) or `.nuspec` to produce a NuGet package.\n\n**Verdict:** Not ready to publish. The JSON structure is valid, but it's missing template content files and a packaging project. The `Framework` symbol also won't take effect without a `replaces` directive.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c0570932-5d6f-41ea-8cc1-50c6130fe8dd","outputTokens":360},"id":"5731a6ac-ed22-44a4-bbc9-0caa11882d32","timestamp":"2026-04-08T00:41:17.959Z","parentId":"ab685274-b12b-4c82-9155-fa9b0e663ecf"}
